cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.ET

This paper involves the use of deep learning for atmospheric correction of satellite imagery, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses uncertainty estimation, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of geostationary satellites and radiative transfer models also suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under graphics (cs.GR) or emerging technologies (cs.ET).
